{
  "article_id": "WeeklyNewsAndDemocrat1885",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "Seventy miles from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the shore",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the sixth of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the group",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "that cluster around the Bay of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara, California",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". It is celebrated for having been the residence for 18 years of \""
      },
      {
        "text": "The Lost Woman of San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".\" As her name is famous and as her story has been told in romance, I will give the bare facts about her as I found them to be, without any added ornament, and leave the fiction to the pen of the novelist."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The "
      },
      {
        "text": "Island of San Nicol[a]s",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was once densely populated. This is attested by the skulls and bones and other evidences of human abode that are found there. The "
      },
      {
        "text": "Alaska Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "frequently visited "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to hunt for the furs of the sea otter. They took their women with them on these hunts, and on returning after the hunt was over they left them on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to their fate. By order of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the government",
        "entity_key": "gov_mexico",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "in 1835, "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroupa",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were removed from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Just before they were to embark, and carry away every human inhabitant, as it was supposed, ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a white Indian woman",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "begged for the privilege of going ashore for ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which she had accidentally left.",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She was gone a long time in a fruitless search for "
      },
      {
        "text": "her offspring",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The wind blew a gale, the water was shallow, there was no one who was seeking "
      },
      {
        "text": "the lost one",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They set sail, intending to return for "
      },
      {
        "text": "the lost woman of San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but "
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "becoming unseaworthy she was left to her fate."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It was generally known that there was "
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "abandoned on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but no attempt was made for her deliverance. As the world soon forgets, so "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman of San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was forgotten, and the year passed away. "
      },
      {
        "text": "After a lapse of sixteen years ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a man",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who landed on ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "found that",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "it was inhabited. The footprints of a human being sunk deep in the ground were seen. The hardness of the ground was an indication that they had been made a long time. From their size they evidently belonged to a woman. Circular inclosures, made of brush, six or seven feet through, were seen, where some one had lived. Near the huts were sticks driven in the ground and dried blubber hanging on them, thus prepared for food."
      }
    ]
  ]
}